  "texts": [
    "However, they differ in terms of the configuration of the energy system.",
    "The experiments are carried out during the cooling season, as a consequence the heating system is not considered.",
    "The cooling system consists of an air-to-water chiller, operating at a constant cold water temperature setpoint (denoted as Tch), and a TES, acting as a buffer between chiller and building and operating at constant water flow rate.",
    "The TES system operates within a temperature range defined between a minimum T s,min and a maximum temperature T s,max.",
    "These temperatures correspond respectively to the maximum and minimum State-Of-Charge (SOC) of the TES system."
  ],
